To add the username         -->     git config --global user.name username
To add the email            -->     git config --global user.email email_id

To check the username and email
    git config user.name    -->     Displays the username
    git config user.email   -->     Displays email_id

To change the directory     -->     cd <path>
To go to previous folder    -->     cd ..
dir                         -->     Will give the list of all the folders and files present in the path
To create a new directory   -->     mkdir dirname
To delete directory         -->     rmdir dirname

To initialize repository    -->     git init
To add files to staging area-->     git add filename
                                    git add folder_name\filename
To add all the files in project --> git add .
To remove the files from the staging area   --> git rm --cached filename

To commit                   -->     git commit -m "descriptive message"
To get details of the commit-->     git log
                                    The above command gives commit_id, author details, message and the timeline of the commit
To get the short details about the commit   --> git log --oneline
                                    The above command will give short commit_id and only the descriptive message

To check the previous commits-->    git checkout <commit_id>

To push the code to github
    *   Create a repository in the github
    *   Every repository will have a url
    *   Copy the url
    *   Open the command prompt
    *   cd <project_path>
    *   add files to staging, then commit(Only committed files can be pushed to the github)
    *   Push the files to the github
        git push repo_url master

Whenever we make the changes in the project and we want to push the changes to the github,
    *   add to staging area
    *   commit
    *   git push repo_url master


To pull the repository from other's github
    *   Get the repo_url
    *   Open the command prompt
    *   cd <project_path>
    *   For the first time we give -->  git clone repo_url
        The repo will be available in the project path
    *   For the next times, to get the changes
        cd <repo_path> -->  git pull
















